Why was my model so high on the Cowboys? There is one pretty easy answer to this solution.
They did not play anybody. McNeese went into the tournament with a record of 30-3, on an eleven game win streak heading into the tournament. It was one of the most picked upsets in all the bracket, but who did they play?
They went on the road and beat the bottom of the Big Ten conference Michigan, the Mississippi University for Women, and the College of Biblical Studies. This was the team the nation was so high on heading into the tournament. They scored a lot, played with great pace, and did not lose much, but their competition was some of the easiest in the entire country.
Even though my model was flawed in many forms, I still was able to predict the national champion, but let’s be real, everyone picked UCONN. If you did not, you did not care about your bracket.
